<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">3</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">May 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">805</span> - <span property="pageEnd">823</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19448117/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19448117</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: May 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.293085715">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=DIR-FSE+%3D+double-inversion-recovery+fast+spin-echo&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">DIR-FSE = double-inversion-recovery fast spin-echo</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ECG+%3D+electrocardiographic&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ECG = electrocardiographic</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SSFP+%3D+steady-state+free+precession&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SSFP = steady-state free precession</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The relevant clinical, MR imaging, and CT findings of acquired disease processes associated with sudden cardiac death are discussed and illustrated, along with imaging techniques and protocols.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Patrick J.</span> <span property="familyName">Sparrow</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Division of Cardiothoracic Imaging, Department of Medical Imaging, University Health Network and Mount Sinai Hospital, 200 Elizabeth St, NCBS 1-562, Toronto, ON, Canada M5G 2C4. Received March 28, 2008; revision requested April 21; final revision received September 10; accepted October 10. N.S.P. received a research grant from Toshiba; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Sparrow/Patrick+J" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Naeem</span> <span property="familyName">Merchant</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Division of Cardiothoracic Imaging, Department of Medical Imaging, University Health Network and Mount Sinai Hospital, 200 Elizabeth St, NCBS 1-562, Toronto, ON, Canada M5G 2C4. Received March 28, 2008; revision requested April 21; final revision received September 10; accepted October 10. N.S.P. received a research grant from Toshiba; all other autho